Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.89,0:00:05.65,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I've never quite been able to sympathize \Nwith a so-called ordinary protagonist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.14,0:00:08.57,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,who longs for an ordinary life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.57,0:00:10.57,sign_206_4_Misumi_Eiichi_an,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Misumi Eiichi and Inflation Battle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.25,0:00:10.57,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.15,0:00:17.32,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to, I'd been playing a puzzle \Ngame at the arcade, my memory missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.02,0:00:20.90,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I was wandering aimlessly \Nthrough the city, when...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.06,0:00:22.85,Flashback Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.85,0:00:24.54,Flashback Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.57,0:00:30.55,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I saved a girl who was being \Nattacked by men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:35.05,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,With her parents' graces, \NI was adopted into her family,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.37,0:00:39.56,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,and I began my life anew as Misumi Eiichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.93,0:00:43.47,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,My basic needs were taken care of, \Nbut my life was not peaceful,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.47,0:00:45.80,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,by any stretch of the imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.80,0:00:48.93,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,The mysterious organization going after \Nmy adoptive sister, Riki, and the glimpses
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.93,0:00:51.69,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,of my past, with which the organization \Nseems to have been involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.93,0:00:52.10,Flashback Dialogue Top,A,0000,0000,0000,,No... Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.10,0:00:54.02,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,My sister, who becomes strangely furious
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:54.89,Flashback Dialogue Top,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,You were talking to someone \Nelse again, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.02,0:00:55.95,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,when I talk about any other girl at school...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:55.95,Flashback Dialogue Top,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.95,0:01:02.83,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I recently joined the gaming club at my \Nnew school, where I endure arduous training.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.83,0:01:06.79,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Having become a participant in \Nthe Total Video Game Tournament,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:14.06,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,also known as TVGT, I defeated \Nmy opponents with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.46,0:01:11.66,Main Dialogue Top,Tennis,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a ways to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.66,0:01:12.96,Main Dialogue Top,Soccer,0000,0000,0000,,The ball is my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:14.49,Main Dialogue Top,What,0000,0000,0000,,It'll work out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.91,0:01:18.22,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,If I win this one, I'm in the finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.22,0:01:20.10,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not letting that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.10,0:01:23.31,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,Your winning streak ends today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:25.85,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself, Eiichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.73,0:01:27.99,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,R-Riki!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.99,0:01:28.81,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.19,0:01:32.91,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't with that \NTendou Karen girl today, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.91,0:01:36.01,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Tendou-san is busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.01,0:01:38.82,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you care, Riki?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.82,0:01:40.07,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:44.58,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I don't hold back in gaming \Ncompetitions. Not even for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:46.18,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.18,0:01:48.54,Main Dialogue,Crayster,0000,0000,0000,,You're going down, Eiichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.42,0:01:56.24,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Tendou-san and Amano-kun \Nare on the bus right about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.24,0:01:58.76,Italics Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they're enjoying their trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:44.47,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Just to confirm, men and women will be \Nsleeping in separate rooms during our trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:46.75,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,We've been given our parents' blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.75,0:03:50.60,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's for just one night, \Nwe must draw a clear line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.60,0:03:52.25,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,That means no flirting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:53.62,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:54.51,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:57.71,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did we even come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.11,0:04:00.98,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It's a serious training camp \Nfor the Gamers Meet-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.98,0:04:02.55,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I get that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.86,0:04:05.02,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be gaming the whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.02,0:04:06.14,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,That's so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:07.94,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.94,0:04:08.67,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.67,0:04:10.23,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally going to be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:13.71,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit worried about this trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.93,0:04:17.79,Italics Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,At least there's no way Hoshinomori \Nwill get left out on a group trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:19.10,Italics Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Plus she's enthusiastic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.10,0:04:20.19,Italics Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:22.07,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Although, Tendou,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:25.86,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,you seem pretty well-prepared for what \Nyou called a "serious training camp."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.50,0:04:27.93,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:31.46,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,This is proper attire for a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.79,0:04:41.51,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:43.09,Main Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.09,0:04:47.22,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Amanocchi. It's not {\i1}that{\i0} hot, \Neven for a bean sprout like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:49.10,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's really hot right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.10,0:04:50.49,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.49,0:04:51.86,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.23,0:04:54.81,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:05:02.32,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Amano-kun, I heard you bought \Nanother obscure game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.32,0:05:04.23,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:06.66,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd found something awesome,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:09.55,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,but I'd actually bought \N{\i1}Elders Hunt{\i0} by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.55,0:05:11.67,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,The game, {\i1}Elders Hunt{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:12.54,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.85,0:05:15.69,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that game that's famous \Nfor being really crappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:16.61,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.61,0:05:19.06,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,And it turns out I can't even return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.06,0:05:21.13,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I wasted a ton of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.13,0:05:23.05,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,That's unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.05,0:05:27.30,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't games kind of \Noverpriced to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:28.30,Italics Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,Gulp...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:32.39,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, they do seem steep when \Nyou see the 6,000 yen price tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.39,0:05:35.27,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,But there are tons of T-shirts that \Nare more expensive, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:37.29,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,No, clothes are worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.29,0:05:38.99,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,They're daily necessities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.99,0:05:41.97,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But games aren't actually \Nuseful for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.97,0:05:44.09,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't 6,000 kinda crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:44.69,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:49.69,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It's nonsense to talk about \Nwhether games are useful or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.69,0:05:53.15,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Going to the movies on a date, \Nindulging in bowling games,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.15,0:05:56.38,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,undressing Amano-kun with your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:05:58.46,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Would you dismiss all of \Nthat as being useless?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:02.00,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'd immediately dismiss \None of those last ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:04.96,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,but movies and bowling are actually fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:07.69,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,G-Gaming is fun, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:08.70,sign_8751_98_Arghhhh_,,0000,0000,0000,,Arghhhh{\c&H2316EC&}!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:08.93,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.53,0:06:13.98,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Your preferences aside, \Ngaming is a kind of recreation, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:18.13,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not a question of \Nwhether it's useful or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.13,0:06:24.44,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I sometimes want to stare \Nat Tendou-san for hours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.43,0:06:26.94,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Amano-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:31.57,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there was no flirting allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:36.21,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Movie stories actually \Nend in around two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.21,0:06:38.30,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,And bowling is exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.30,0:06:42.71,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But games are, like, just a way \Nto bleep-bloop your life away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.71,0:06:45.30,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, \N"bleep-bloop your life away"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:46.33,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.74,0:06:49.93,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,For modern humans such as ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:57.30,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,living such barren lives, \Ngaming is not a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:58.68,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshinomori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:58.68,Main Dialogue Top,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Chiaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:03.86,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Gamers don't really look happy the \Nwhole time they're gaming, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.21,0:07:08.23,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a pain in the butt \Nto level up and stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.85,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.85,0:07:14.87,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,G-Games are fun, leveling up included!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:15.94,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.94,0:07:20.77,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Amanocchi told me about how people \Npass out in the middle of a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:24.75,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Would that ever happen if \Nleveling up were actually fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:25.88,Italics Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,She's too astute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.38,0:07:32.68,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What's fun about trying to stay awake \Ngrinding for experience points?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.69,0:07:38.72,Main Dialogue,Eh itchy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but there are techniques to \Nmultitask while you're leveling up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:41.10,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you can do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:43.27,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Gamers must be really smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.67,0:07:46.86,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,It's embarrassing when you put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:51.86,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that just admitting that \Nleveling up is really boring?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.81,0:07:59.63,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, this looks way too nice for student trips.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:01.85,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,This looks amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.85,0:08:03.42,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You go, Tendou-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:04.34,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.34,0:08:06.01,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,So what are we doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:09.49,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Gamers Meet-up trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:10.92,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,What else would we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:13.01,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Gaming, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:17.55,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,They come all the way out here to play games?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:22.10,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:27.88,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,So new games do start at around 6,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.88,0:08:29.29,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.29,0:08:30.94,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,This game's over 10,000 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:35.53,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, it's bundled with concept \Nart and a DLC for in-game use?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:38.52,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, what's a "DLC" again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.52,0:08:40.95,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,It stands for "downloadable content."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.95,0:08:45.50,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, you get access \Nto character costumes online.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:50.06,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,So you're paying real money for clothes \Nthat the characters wear in the game?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.06,0:08:50.84,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.69,0:08:55.31,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in those kinds of DLCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:56.73,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me, neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:09:00.85,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You say that like you would \Nbuy other kinds, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.23,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I buy swimsuit costumes and stuff, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.90,0:09:06.35,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.15,0:09:12.42,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, you were like, "It makes no \Nsense to compare games to T-shirts."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.89,0:09:14.95,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're going to buy clothes \Nfor game characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.95,0:09:17.36,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't {\i1}that{\i0} money be better \Nspent on your own clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:22.24,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Game characters are kind \Nof reflections of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.24,0:09:26.06,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,It's fair to say it's the same thing \Nas buying clothes in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.06,0:09:27.03,Main Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.03,0:09:28.18,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:31.94,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still not sure about spending money \Non things that aren't actually useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:34.25,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,They {\i1}are{\i0} useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.25,0:09:35.74,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.74,0:09:36.26,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:42.39,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Aguri-san, what would you do \Nif Uehara-kun bought you a ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:44.02,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What? Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.02,0:09:46.58,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be really happy, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:50.22,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Then if you got the ring, would you equip it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.22,0:09:51.18,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Or would you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.18,0:09:52.40,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Equip it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.40,0:09:53.67,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You mean wear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.67,0:09:55.86,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'd equip it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:59.26,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Would your love for Uehara-kun \Ngrow as a result?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.87,0:10:04.70,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I-I guess, sure. I like gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:05.56,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:09.67,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, you've accepted \Nthe concept of DLCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:12.02,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.02,0:10:12.74,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.74,0:10:13.96,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,That's totally different!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:17.86,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what it means: \NUehara-kun would have bought
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.86,0:10:21.34,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,an item that increases attraction stats \Nfor a bishoujo character named Aguri-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:22.81,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,using real money!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.81,0:10:23.98,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:25.81,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,It just sounds wrong \Nwhen you say it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.20,0:10:27.35,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.35,0:10:31.57,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,If Tasuku were to somehow \Nbecome a digital entity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.57,0:10:34.85,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I might pay for so-called \Npremium items to give him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.85,0:10:35.51,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:39.22,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, if I were to \N"somehow" become a digital entity?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.22,0:10:43.89,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, if changing your \Navatar's outfit and equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.89,0:10:48.66,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,were to cause digital Uehara-kun to turn \Nred or become shy, what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:51.08,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Premium items, please! How much are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.08,0:10:52.07,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.07,0:10:54.63,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are seriously making \Nsome crazy assumptions!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.63,0:10:55.60,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Aguri...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.60,0:11:01.05,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You don't have to do that. I-I already...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.75,0:11:03.80,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tasuku...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.05,0:11:10.71,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Buy a loot box with a chance to win \Nthis agonizing event for just 300 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.71,0:11:13.21,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm buying a hundred of those, Amanocchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.21,0:11:14.45,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.45,0:11:14.95,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:17.07,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Quit using me to mess with my girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.31,0:11:21.66,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,30,000 yen to buy Tasuku's sweet nothings?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:22.68,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,That's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:24.58,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Aguri, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.08,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,I'm plenty fun free-to-play!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:31.29,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm serious about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.67,0:11:32.79,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Tasuku...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:37.59,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how the free game industry \Nlures you in these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:38.84,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.84,0:11:39.85,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,That's very informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:41.80,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:45.22,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I totally get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:47.56,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:48.64,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Games are...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:51.73,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Games are real shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.97,0:11:55.42,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.97,0:12:15.86,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,About what we were saying, games these days \Nmake you pay a ton of money up front,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:18.63,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,but then they don't let you \Nenjoy the whole thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:22.01,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,See? The reviews are horrible, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.59,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,"Paid players have too much of an \Nadvantage in multiplayer games."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:28.25,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,"It's a typical pay-to-win game."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.30,0:12:28.25,Main Dialogue Top,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, that's cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.25,0:12:34.90,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,"The single player story isn't even finished.\NI feel like I've been sold an unfinished product."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.47,0:12:34.90,Main Dialogue Top,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,That's a rip-off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.63,0:12:38.57,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not all games are like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:41.73,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like this series is big, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.73,0:12:45.42,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a sign that the \Nindustry is in its final days?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.42,0:12:49.14,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,D-DLCs themselves aren't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.14,0:12:54.66,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get excited when your favorite \Nmanga gets a spin-off after it finishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.66,0:12:56.93,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:13:01.93,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there's nothing wrong \Nwith DLCs that the users request.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.07,0:13:06.05,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Then what kind of DLC would make you happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:08.90,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, your favorite character's swim—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.90,0:13:12.81,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,What else but a higher difficulty mode?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.45,0:13:15.70,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.70,0:13:17.02,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,This place is so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:19.38,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It's so big, and the view is so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.38,0:13:20.77,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.77,0:13:25.09,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But a higher difficulty mode just makes \Nthe game even harder to play, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.09,0:13:28.49,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I really don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:32.71,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it feel great when you \Nachieve a really challenging goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.71,0:13:35.37,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I get that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.73,0:13:40.14,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,And when you're being tortured \Nby a cruelly difficult game,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.14,0:13:43.63,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't it actually start to feel {\i1}good{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:46.38,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I have no idea \Nwhat you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:50.15,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about how pain feels good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.15,0:13:53.79,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, this is weird... I thought \Nwe were talking about games,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:57.14,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,but now I'm listening to you open up \Nabout your weird sexual fetishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:13:58.18,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.18,0:14:01.67,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just me. All gamers are like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:02.23,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.23,0:14:03.11,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:09.11,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:13.10,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I want games \Nto be more challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.10,0:14:17.92,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, all the hardcore gamers \Nin the game club would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:21.79,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know that the game club members \Nare all complete masochists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:24.14,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You're a bunch of deviants who get together
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:26.88,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,to stare ecstatically at \Nunfair game-over screens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:28.42,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,That's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.38,0:14:32.93,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, you're not {\i1}totally{\i0} wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.93,0:14:33.81,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:39.36,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then gamers are all masochistic deviants?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.36,0:14:40.68,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.68,0:14:42.34,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.34,0:14:48.40,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, it makes me really happy \Nto see the epilogue after an RPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:51.50,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.50,0:14:54.87,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when, like, \Nthe human hero and heroine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.87,0:14:57.58,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,suddenly turn into fish \Nand there's a huge panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:15:01.27,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,That would be the most fantastic epilogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:04.29,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's creepy as hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:06.71,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry if I gave you the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:10.97,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,I'm assuming the actual RPG \Nwas a classic fantasy RPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:12.93,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought otherwise!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.29,0:15:18.06,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It'd actually make more sense to me if the \Ncharacters were animals to begin with!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:21.19,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,That's silly, Aguri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:24.81,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,It's the proper human visuals in \Nthe main story that put emphasis
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.81,0:15:28.25,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,on the fish stuff in the \Nepilogue and make it fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.70,0:15:33.90,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is the first time in my life \NI'm looking insanity in the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.90,0:15:34.53,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,That's rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:39.37,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who takes pride in being a gamer \Ndesires a fish-morphing epilogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.37,0:15:40.39,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:48.65,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Although, I guess some people \Nprefer something other than fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.65,0:15:50.84,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think that's the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.84,0:15:55.19,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,But DLCs are the same thing as \Nspin-offs and companion media.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.19,0:15:58.27,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want them to go all-out \Nin ways they can't in the main game?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:16:02.10,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that kind of makes sense, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:03.25,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.25,0:16:07.02,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,If there was a fish version of your favorite \Nmanga, you'd want to read it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:09.01,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so confused!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:11.18,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,A combat manga, set on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.18,0:16:13.61,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,about evolved cockroaches and fish \Nwho fight with special abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:16.38,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gilla Formars{\i0}! Wouldn't that be awesome?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:18.20,Main Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you invade us, {\i1}bass{\i0}tard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:20.39,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, damn. I might want to read that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.39,0:16:25.75,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Though the good guys, physiologically, \Ncan only survive underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:28.55,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gilla Formars{\i0} wouldn't \Nwork on Mars at all, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:34.85,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, DLCs ought to be completely removed \Nand crazy, compared to the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.85,0:16:38.55,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like you have a point, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.55,0:16:40.18,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:44.11,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:45.62,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.62,0:16:49.61,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I'm curious about what \NAmano-kun's talking about or anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:55.02,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I think I prefer epilogue DLCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.02,0:16:55.91,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Normal ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.18,0:17:01.16,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Also, part of me doesn't hate the \Nidea of plain hard mode DLCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.16,0:17:03.90,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You're too normal, Amanocchi. It's no fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.90,0:17:05.30,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,What's it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.30,0:17:08.93,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You don't really make a good derp.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.93,0:17:11.84,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I live my life \Ntrying to be the derpy guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.84,0:17:15.25,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, you don't have glasses, \Nso you can't be the straight man, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.25,0:17:18.90,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,No one ever told me you need glasses \Nto be the straight man!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.90,0:17:21.53,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you buy a glasses DLC?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.53,0:17:23.62,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,No way! I don't want that \Nkind of additional content!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:25.85,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I'll chip in 2,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:28.25,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,It kind of pisses me off that they're so cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.43,0:17:33.59,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,You two are having fun, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.17,0:17:39.29,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.08,0:17:49.19,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.19,0:17:51.26,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,That's against the rules, Aguri-san!
