Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.79,0:17:54.96,sign_25746_323_Sakurano,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,1)}Sakurano
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:54.96,sign_25758_324_President_Keita_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,President Keita has arrived\Nat Sakurano!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:57.68,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,So the DLC that I want...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:18:01.61,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,What about one that shows the hero \Nand heroine happily living together?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.61,0:18:04.09,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,How is that even a game anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.09,0:18:05.39,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.39,0:18:08.30,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,But the plot is already \Nresolved in the main story,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.30,0:18:10.65,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,so I would feel sorry for the characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:13.94,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,starting a new conflict just \Nbecause I want to play more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:16.66,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is your perspective, Keita?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.54,0:18:20.38,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,He's as lukewarm and kind-hearted as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:24.78,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I kind of understand \Nhow the DLC system works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.78,0:18:29.46,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It's like ordering dessert or\Nextra toppings at a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:30.57,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.57,0:18:32.06,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good analogy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.06,0:18:37.53,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,And the bad reviews are because the main \Ndish was served bland, and they're like,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.53,0:18:42.65,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,"Oh, it's an extra 300 yen for a \Nshake of salt," so they're upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:50.87,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,So after everything I heard, I still feel like \Ngames are too expensive, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.87,0:18:54.25,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Something doesn't sit right about \Nthe way they screw you over,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.25,0:18:57.69,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,demanding another few \Nthousand yen on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:00.61,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.61,0:19:04.51,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I'm trying to criticize games, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:11.08,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think what you say stings \Nfor anyone who plays a lot of games.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.18,0:19:15.84,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,So gamers are all super masochistic, \Nlike Tendou-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:18.38,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Tendou-san's the only one \Nwho's as masochistic as she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:19.35,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Amano-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.35,0:19:20.97,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,It really doesn't sound like a joke
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.97,0:19:24.24,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,when your boyfriend says \Nyou're super masochistic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.24,0:19:27.98,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, I think games \Nmight be a form of recreation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:31.10,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,that's especially open to wastefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.67,0:19:35.13,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You're happy about wasting money?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.13,0:19:39.25,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,For example, I have a game at home \Nthat my parents bought for me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.25,0:19:41.18,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,when I was in elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.18,0:19:45.55,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually a crappy rip-off that's more \Nexpensive than the game it's a clone of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.55,0:19:47.01,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, what a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.01,0:19:48.43,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.43,0:19:50.51,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,My parents bought it by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:52.76,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have the heart to tell \Nthem it was the wrong one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:55.25,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,That story hits close to home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:20:00.32,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,But once you try playing it, \Nyou start to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.32,0:20:04.70,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up playing it for three years, \Ncomplaining the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:11.11,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,That is a nice story, but I think it \Ncould happen even if it weren't a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:17.50,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was only memorable \Nbecause it was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.49,0:20:23.81,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Games are also a flexible medium \Nthat give you the freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.81,0:20:26.78,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,to make as much of an emotional \Ninvestment as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.74,0:20:33.95,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say whether games are more \Nexpensive than other entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.95,0:20:39.30,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,There are always going to be some games \Nyou buy that turn out to be terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.89,0:20:44.66,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,But that's exactly why the only \Nthing that we gamers can do
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.66,0:20:49.43,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,is to enjoy games to the best of \Nour ability, each in our own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.25,0:20:56.21,Main Dialogue,Tacky,0000,0000,0000,,I guess bandwagoning around bad \Nreviews is one way to have fun, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.21,0:20:57.42,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.42,0:21:00.57,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, as in Amano-kun's story,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.57,0:21:04.57,Main Dialogue,Tender,0000,0000,0000,,that can lead to it becoming a memorable \Ngame that's more precious than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.57,0:21:05.71,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.71,0:21:10.25,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,There are websites that rank terrible games.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.25,0:21:12.82,Main Dialogue,Cheeky,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's the kind of secondary \Nvalue that games have a lot of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:15.85,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, \Nthat crappy game I got
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.85,0:21:20.80,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,is worth way more than just a \Nfew thousand yen to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.53,0:21:27.90,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,So... do you appreciate why \Ngames cost so much now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:30.17,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.17,0:21:34.52,Main Dialogue,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I won't say games are too expensive \Nor anything like that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.43,0:21:39.02,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.71,0:21:46.68,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.68,0:21:52.04,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,now that we know {\i1}every{\i0} game offers a \Nway to be enjoyed, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.46,0:21:59.29,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we play the infamous, terrible, \Nfive-player action game, {\i1}Elders Hunt{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.04,0:22:03.22,Main Dialogue,A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Goodnight!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.79,0:22:10.30,Main Dialogue,Katie,0000,0000,0000,,I want a refund.
